data.title: Joanne Linville obituary
data.meta_description: The romance between Joanne Linville’s Romulan commander and the Vulcan officer Spock, played by Leonard Nimoy, could have been the greatest intergalactic alien
data.text:
The romance between Joanne Linville’s Romulan commander and the Vulcan officer Spock, played by Leonard Nimoy, could have been the greatest intergalactic alien love story of the 23rd century.

Their flirtation happened in an episode in 1968’s third series of Star Trek, in which Linville’s character falls for Spock after taking him and other members of the Starship Enterprise’s crew aboard her spaceship for violating Romulan space. Spock ends up in the commander’s quarters and Romulan and Vulcan get up-close and extra-terrestrially personal. Yet as every Trekkie knows, Vulcans live by logic and reason alone and eschew emotion, and so it is merely a ploy by Spock to create a distraction and get Linville to drop her guard.
